#import "/formatting.typ": *

#let fns = (
  meat: fn[I'd recommend frying beef after having let it soak in a beef marinade for 12-24
    hours. Sausage & ham work fine too, though you need plenty of ham for ham to work.],
)

#show: recipe.with(
  title: "Barszcz",
  panel-width: 40%,
  description: [
    Red beet soup. Polish spelling. #footnote[Alternate names include: Борщ
      (:flag_ukr:/:flag_rus:), Borsch(t) (direct transliteration), Боршч (:flag_blr:),
      Borshch (direct transliteration), ...
    ]
  ],
)[


  #sb[Broth:]
  - Beets
  - Cabbage
  - Carrots
  - One large onion
  - Salt & seasonings to taste #aside[OR: #url[chicken bouillon]]
  - Splash of vinegar
  - Water #LS

  #sb[Extra:]
  - Meat#fns.meat, cooked
  - Fried potatoes, medium chunks #LS

  #sb[Toppings:]
  - Cream
  - Dill
]

Add as much or as little of each ingredient as you'd like. All ingredients aside from
beets, salt, and water are optional. #LS


+ Dice beets into large chunks and carrots & onion into small chunks.
+ Mix broth ingredients in a large pot. Season as desired.
+ Boil broth until beets are cooked throughout. While this is happening, you may want to
  cook your meat & potatoes.
+ After water cools down somewhat, toss meat & potatoes into broth.
+ Serve fresh. Top with dill & cream.
